ONE OF the two tallest men to ever play basketball for the NBA in America is a son of the African soil.Manute Bol s official height, according to the Guinness Book of World Records, is listed as 2 305m. He basically had to bend his knees to enter any room!Manute, meaning special blessing, was born in Sudan in 1962. His claim to fame in US basketball was his amazing ability to block shots. He blocked more shots from opposition teams than he ever scored the only NBA player to do so.Manute supported many charitable causes in his country Sudan, visiting refugee camps and giving most of his fortune to aiding the displaced in the war-torn country.He died of kidney problems and a serious skin disorder in 2010.One of his sons, Bol Bol, is a star basketball player in the making.